quran[47]{c,v,t}:
  26,181,"Give full measure, and do not cheat"
  26,182,Weigh with an even scale
  26,183,"and do not mislead people into thinking that their goods are worth less than their real value, and do not spread corruption on earth"
  26,184,Fear Him who created you and the former generations
  26,185,"They said, \"You are surely bewitched"
  26,186,"You are a man like us, and we think you are a liar"
  26,187,"Make a fragment of the sky fall on us, if you are telling the truth"
  26,188,"He said, \"My Lord knows best what you are doing"
  26,189,"But they did not believe him, and the punishment of the day of shadow seized them truly, the punishment of a terrible day"
  26,190,"There is a sign in this, but most of them will not believe"
  26,191,"Truly your Lord is the Almighty, the Merciful-to-all"
  26,192,"This [Qur'an] is the revelation sent as you received it from the Lord of the worlds"
  26,193,and brought down by The Trustworthy Spirit
  26,194,"to your heart, that you may (Prophet] be of the warners"
  26,195,"in a clear perfected [Arabic] tongue"
  26,196,It is mentioned in the scriptures of the ancients
  26,197,Is it not a sign that the scholars of the Children of Israel knew it
  26,198,Yet even if We had revealed it to a non-Arab
  26,199,"and he had recited it to them, they would still not believe in it"
  26,200,This is how We make it go unheeded through the hearts of those who force others to reject Our messages
  26,201,they will not believe until they see the painful punishment
  26,202,"that will come upon them suddenly, when they do not expect it"
  26,203,"They will say, \"May we have more time"
  26,204,Why do they ask that we hasten Our punishment
  26,205,"Do you see that, if We gave them years of enjoyment"
  26,206,then inflicted the punishment as promised
  26,207,what good would the years of enjoyment be to them
  26,208,We have never destroyed a town without sending messengers to warn
  26,209,"and remind it, for We have never been unjust"
  26,210,"The devils did not bring it [this Qur'an] down"
  26,211,"They are not able, nor are they capable"
  26,212,"As they are indeed barred from hearing [what goes on around the throne of His majesty]"
  26,213,"So do not invoke another deity beside God, or you will incur punishment"
  26,214,Warn your closest relatives
  26,215,and be humble and kind to the believers who follow you
  26,216,"but, if they disobey you, then say, \"I am not responsible for what you are doing"
  26,217,"And rely upon the Almighty, the Merciful-to-all"
  26,218,Who sees you when you arise
  26,219,and when you move among those who prostrate themselves
  26,220,"He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing"
  26,221,Shall I inform you upon whom the devils descend
  26,222,They descend upon every sinful liar
  26,223,"who readily lends an ear, but most of them are liars"
  26,224,"As for the poets, [only] the perverse follow them"
  26,225,Do you not see that they wander aimlessly in every valley
  26,226,and say what they do not do
  26,227,"But except those [poets) who believe, do righteous deeds, remember God often, and defend themselves after they were wronged. Those who do wrong will soon know the kind of reversal they will receive"